Adolfina, 43 years old, is a mother of six children. She is a single parent after a divorce, and she patiently and diligently performs her work as a banana seller at Inpres traditional market in Kupang.  Her six children are:
1.	Ersy, 25 years old is married;
2.	Merlin, 23 years old, is married;
3.	Erdin, 14 years old, in the 2nd grade of Junior high school;
4.	Frans, 11 years old, in the 5th grade of Elementary school;
5.	Selfina, 8 years old, in the 2nd grade of Elementary school; and
6.	Santika, a-6-year-old, in kindergarten.

As a single parent, Adolfina is a strong woman.  She leaves home and heads to the market to sell bananas from 6 am to 8 p.m. She has to be patient to wait until the bananas are sold out.  Adolfina is quite aware that selling bananas is not enough to meet the daily needs of her family.  She also needs to pay for four of her children's schooling.  She really wants to overcome her financial issues by creating another business instead of just selling bananas. 

She is planning to breed pigs near her house.  She requests loan assistance amounting to IDR 4,500,000 to purchase a pair of piglets and  to make a pig cage.  She will also buy food to begin. She really hopes that the loan assistance can improve her financial status and also can change her family's life in the future.
